ProvisionDesc.Name: Local Call Feature
ProvisionDesc.Help:
Dial the feature prefix followed by 'code*1#' to enable feature, 'code*0#' to disable feature, 'code*number#' to configure number, and 'code*#' to return to the default value.
The code 0~19 are reserved for speed dialing. Setting the code to 0 disables configuration of the local feature by phone.
Codes can be piggybacked without the prefix. E.g. dial the feature prefix followed by 'code1*1#code2*1#code3*0#' enableds feature1 and feature2 while disables feature3.
Clearing the feature prefix disables configuration of all local features by phone.

SettingDesc.Name: Feature Profile
SettingDesc.Help:
Profile numbers above 127 are reserved for individual line.
If "Pound Sign key" is enabled, the dialed numbers prior to the pound sign '#' are sent out immediately without waiting for digit timeout. If disabled, the pound sign '#' will be sent as dialed number.
Please note Pound Sign key is only effective if digitmap is disabled or the number is not matched to the digitmap in voice profile.

SettingDesc.Name: Hunt Group
SettingDesc.Help:
Linear: ring one member line at a time, always start with the first member.
Circular: ring one member line at a time, the beginning member is shifted circularly every time.
Ring All: ring all member lines every time.

SettingDesc.Name: Dialing Plan
SettingDesc.Help: If Voice Profile is not selected, this is a global rule.
